# Frontend App (`apps/app`)

TypeScript only. Layers: `agent-discipline.mdc`. Storybook: `frontend-storybook.mdc`. Design system: `frontend-design-system.mdc`. Client perf: `react-performance.mdc`. Backend: `backend-execution.mdc`.

## Next.js — MCP, not memory

1. `nextjs-docs://llms-index` → `nextjs_docs` (`/docs/app/guides/ai-agents`)
2. MCP `init` with `project_path: apps/app`
3. Dev server up → `nextjs_index` → `nextjs_call` `get_errors` before claiming UI work is done

## Where app UI lives

| Path | Use for |
|------|---------|
| `apps/app/app/` | Pages, layouts, route segments |
| `apps/app/app/(authenticated)/components/` | Authenticated shell wiring |
| `apps/app/app/actions/` | Server Actions |

Visual/polish → app wiring or Storybook first. Design-system primitives require human approval.

## Server vs Client Components

Default **Server Components**. `'use client'` only for state, events, hooks, or browser APIs.

- Push client boundary to the **smallest** interactive leaf
- Server `children` into Client wrappers; thin Client providers in layout
- **`params` and `searchParams` are `Promise`** — `await` in Server Components (Next.js 16)

```tsx
export default async function Page(props: PageProps<'/items/[id]'>) {
  const { id } = await props.params
  const item = await getItem(id)
  return <ItemActions item={item} />
}
```

Runtime/uncached data → `<Suspense>`. Cache: MCP `/docs/app/getting-started/caching`.

## Styling & imports

- Tailwind + `cn()` from `@repo/design-system/lib/utils`
- Primitives: `@repo/design-system/components/ui/*`
- Provider: `@repo/design-system` (`DesignSystemProvider`)
- Web UI MUST rules: `web-interface-interactions.mdc`, `web-interface-accessibility.mdc`
- Server-only logic: `@repo/*` packages with `server-only` — never import from client components
- `next/link`, `next/image` with explicit sizes

## Anti-patterns

```tsx
// ❌ Whole layout client for one button
'use client'
export default function DashboardLayout({ children }) { /* ... */ }

// ❌ Sync params
const { id } = params

// ✅ Await params; minimal client boundary
const { id } = await props.params
```

